response.overview: This humble brag travelogue documents Watch This Space big-boss @alopeno’s trip to a Venice Biennale through DV cam footage of all the dogs he saw along the way. Full of joy and generosity, Charlie Freedman’s Dogs in Venice is a movie you send to your little Venice Bitch when they’re missing you, and Italianx food porn is too much. Italy is an island, and a boot, and Dogs in Space is a movie about share houses. Charlie, with Lucie McMahon, started the Dead End Film Festival which showed and defined Resourceful Films from around the world at the Coburg Drive In Cinema with performances and writing. To be continued…
response.title: Dogs In Venice
